# character/.gitignore — the transient-vs-permanent boundary, which is not housekeeping
# but philosophy: WHAT SURVIVES THE RESET DEFINES THE SELF. Tracked = the character's
# durable substance (memory, workbench, corpus, the shared page). Ignored = what one
# life holds and the next should not inherit as record: the drawer, transient state,
# things shown in passing. If you add a live-channel store (chat dispatches, feeds),
# ignore it — outside talk is weather, not marrow.
#
# The .gitkeep pattern keeps every ignored path alive for the character's reads even
# when its contents are wiped.

# The drawer: unsent, for no one — kept out of the record entirely.
drafts/*
!drafts/.gitkeep
!drafts/README.md

# Hook bookkeeping: machine state, not the character's record.
.claude/slate-state.json
.claude/hooks/mood-state.txt

# Machine-local settings, if you split any out.
.claude/settings.local.json
